"I began my photography journey with an action camera because I was interested in the distortion effect. But after a year, I got bored and got a DSLR for its flexibility and versatility. I can always change lenses and perspectives depending on the kind of shot I was planning. It took me about 2-3 months to save enough for the camera because I'm still a student. Now I use it to shoot mostly portraits and I'm eyeing the EF85mm f/1.8 USM to get better and sharper images with nice bokeh.” See the results of Luqman Nurhaqim's work at @luqmann_____ on Instagram, and tag us in photos of your Canon gear for a chance to be featured!

Funny story 
I always wanted to go to Cambodia , up until last year where I booked with my friend from Saigon to Cambodia,  as a Jordanian I can obtain a visa on arrival,  when I reached the Cambodian border point,  gave them my passport and the officer was like oh you can not enter,  and he started to ask me how much money do I have,  and I didn't have more than 50$ because I won't take 2000$ with me on the road because I know I'd lose them am seriously clumsy,  after going forth and back with him because he clearly wanted to get a bribe and I refused,  he wouldn't let me enter,  worst day ever so I had to go back to Vietnam. Cambodia still on my list and am going this year for sure,  but I'll use the damn airport instead of the land border,  @theroyalbubblemaker  still hates me for being unorganized  haha,  also this amazing picture was taken by her so please do follow.

A girl looks out from a window of her house gutted in a devastating fire on April 5th. The fire claimed more than 25 structures in Dal Lake, Srinagar, Indian controlled Kashmir.

Over a month has passed, but the affected families are still living in tents in this harsh weather, left at the mercy of God.
